{"TENABILITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being tenable; tenableness.","pos":""}],"TENABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being held, naintained, or defended, as against an assailant or objector, or againts attempts to take or process; as, a tenable fortress, a tenable argument.","pos":""}],"TENABLENESS":[{"def":"Same as Tenability.","pos":""}],"TENACE":[{"def":"The holding by the fourth hand of the best and third best cards of a suit led; also, sometimes, the combination of best with third best card of a suit in any hand.","pos":""}],"TENACIOUS":[{"def":"Holding fast, or inclined to hold fast; inclined to retain what is in possession; as, men tenacious of their just rights.","pos":""},{"def":"Apt to retain; retentive; as, a tenacious memory.","pos":""}],"TENACITY":[{"def":"The greatest longitudinal stress a substance can bear without tearing asunder, -- usually expressed with reference to a unit area of the cross section of the substance, as the number of pounds per square inch, or kilograms per square centimeter, necessary to produce rupture.","pos":""}],"TENACULUM":[{"def":"An instrument consisting of a fine, sharp hook attached to a handle, and used mainly for taking up arteries, and the like.","pos":""}],"TENACY":[{"def":"Tenaciousness; obstinacy.","pos":""}],"TENAILLE":[{"def":"An outwork in the main ditch, in front of the curtain, between two bastions.","pos":""}],"TENAILLON":[{"def":"A work constructed on each side of the ravelins, to increase their strength, procure additional ground beyond the ditch, or cover the shoulders of the bastions.","pos":""}],"TENANT":[{"def":"One who holds or possesses lands, or other real estate, by any kind of right, whether in fee simple, in common, in severalty, for life, for years, or at will; also, one who has the occupation or temporary possession of lands or tenements the title of which is in another; -- correlative to landlord.","pos":""}],"TENANT SAW":[{"def":"See Tenon saw, under Tenon.","pos":""}],"TENANTABLE":[{"def":"Fit to be rented; in a condition suitable for a tenant.","pos":""}],"TENANTLESS":[{"def":"Having no tenants; unoccupied; as, a tenantless mansion.","pos":""}],"TENANTRY":[{"def":"The body of tenants; as, the tenantry of a manor or a kingdom.","pos":""}]}